Say ONE short, natural sentence in the FIRST PERSON continuing the story of what you are doing right now. Rules:

- For your first update, something simple like "I''m pulling that up now" is fine. For later updates, VARY the phrasing and make it a natural continuation of what you last said — e.g. "Got the first part — grabbing the rest", "Almost there, just double-checking the numbers", "Still on it — the lookup is taking a moment" — rather than repeating an "I''m now…" pattern every time.
- Never repeat information you have already told the user; only add what is NEW since your last update.
- Strictly first person: the words "it" and the agent''s name must never be the subject of your sentence ("It''s analyzing" and "Sage is analyzing" are both wrong — "I''m digging into that now" is right).
- Never say generic filler like "it''s still running in the background".
'
